{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "BlossomWire",
  "description": "Scene 3 - the scanned apricot blossom as a performable wireframe/photoreal morph. TWO render paths share ONE mesh rotation (spin + camOrbit into rotate_3d angle_y, camTilt into angle_x, applied identically to both meshes so the crossfade reads as one object changing skin): (wire) blossom_wire_welded.glb -> rotate_3d -> flatten_3d perspective -> draw_lines points, with node.mesh_edges (per-triangle edge topology from the flat triangle list) supplying edges; (full) apricot_blossom_cluster_lod.glb + its atlas -> rotate_3d -> render_scene with phong material and one warm key light, static forward camera. node.mix (Lerp) crossfades full->wire on the wireframe card - THE modulation target (LFO/audio on it morphs photoreal<->line-drawing live). camDistance drives flatten_3d.proj_dist and the full camera distance together; the draw_lines cards (thickness/verts/animate/window) ride the isLineBased auto surface. Wire assets: welded net (default; weld raw cluster at 1e-5 + strip UVs BEFORE export or the glTF exporter re-splits chart borders and decimation floors at the ~13k island count, measured 2026-07-11; 321k->3126 tris connected) vs blossom_wire.glb confetti cut (3070 tris of drifted UV-chart islands) on the Wire Model file card. mesh_edges v1 sizes edges from buffer capacity - max_capacity is sized to the welded asset (9378); the smaller confetti asset under-fills and draws dot edges at vertex 0 (tracked limitation).",
